  "body": "*Title*: Add support for subset load balancing to `envoy.tcp_proxy`\r\n\r\n*Context*:\r\n\r\nI\u2019m trying to configure Envoy to use load balancer subsets at L4.\r\n\r\nE.g., I want to dispatch 10% of traffic to endpoints marked as \u201cmaster\u201d and 90% to endpoints marked as \u201creplica\u201d.\r\n\r\nIdeally, my configuration should look like\r\n\r\n```\r\nname: envoy.tcp_proxy\r\ntypedConfig:\r\n  '@type': type.googleapis.com/envoy.config.filter.network.tcp_proxy.v2.TcpProxy\r\n  statPrefix: postgres.internal:5432\r\n  weighted_clusters:\r\n    clusters:\r\n    - name: postgres.internal:5432\r\n      metadata_match:                       # NOTE: there is no `metadata_match` field at the moment\r\n        filter_metadata:                    #\r\n          envoy.lb:                         #\r\n            role: master                    #\r\n      weight: 10\r\n    - name: postgres.internal:5432\r\n      metadata_match:                       # NOTE: there is no `metadata_match` field at the moment\r\n        filter_metadata:                    #\r\n          envoy.lb:                         #\r\n            role: replica                   #\r\n      weight: 90\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, `envoy.tcp_proxy` does not support `metadata_match` per weighted cluster at the moment.\r\n\r\n*Proposal*:\r\n\r\n* add `metadata_match` field to `TcpProxy.WeightedCluster.ClusterWeight` (similarly to `route.WeightedCluster.ClusterWeight`)\r\n* use `metadata_match` field to enable subset load balancing at `envoy.tcp_proxy`\r\n",
